/-- A normed space over a normed field is a vector space endowed with a norm which satisfies the
equality `‚Äñc ‚Ä¢ x‚Äñ = ‚Äñc‚Äñ ‚Äñx‚Äñ`. We require only `‚Äñc ‚Ä¢ x‚Äñ ‚â§ ‚Äñc‚Äñ ‚Äñx‚Äñ` in the definition, then prove
